  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7114 sitting just below the max negative gamma strike at 7115, dealers are currently net short gamma here and will be buying the dip as price pulls back from the -2.5% 5-minute decline. The massive positive gamma wall at 7200 (+8.2B) acts as a strong ceiling where dealers will aggressively sell any rally attempts, while the PIN regime supports mean-reversion behavior around current levels. Key levels to watch are the 7115 negative gamma pivot for continued dealer buying support and the 7100/7150 positive gamma walls that should contain price action.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect choppy trading between 7100-7150 with dealers providing support on dips and resistance on rallies.",
